The paper discusses a new framework for defining abductive reasoning operators in arbitrary logics, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of satisfaction systems and retraction is particularly relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the application of the framework to different logics, which could be relevant to computer science theory (cs.CC) and programming languages (cs.PL). Overall, the paper could fit into several sub-categories, but cs.AI and cs.LO seem to be the most relevant.
